The paper deals with computer vision problems such as image and scene recognition, and proposes a similarity learning network for one- and few-shot learning. The paper also discusses the use of Power Normalizations, which are non-linear activation units that can be applied in CNNs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training the model end-to-end, which suggests the involvement of machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper involves the use of probability-inspired derivations, which suggests the involvement of statistical techniques, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the problem of one- and few-shot learning, which suggests the involvement of natural language processing techniques, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category.
